.TH "batadv_dat_check_dhcp_ack" 9 "batadv_dat_check_dhcp_ack" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
batadv_dat_check_dhcp_ack \- examine packet for valid DHCP message
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "bool" batadv_dat_check_dhcp_ack
.BI "(struct sk_buff *skb "  ","
.BI "__be16 proto "  ","
.BI "__be32 *ip_src "  ","
.BI "u8 *chaddr "  ","
.BI "__be32 *yiaddr "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "skb" 12
the packet to check
.IP "proto" 12
ethernet protocol hint (behind a potential vlan)
.IP "ip_src" 12
a buffer to store the IPv4 source address in
.IP "chaddr" 12
a buffer to store the DHCP Client Hardware Address in
.IP "yiaddr" 12
a buffer to store the DHCP Your IP Address in
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Checks whether the given skb is a valid DHCPACK. And if so, stores the
IPv4 server source address (ip_src), client MAC address (chaddr) and client
IPv4 address (yiaddr) in the provided buffers.

Caller needs to ensure that the skb network header is set correctly.
.SH "RETURN"
True if the skb is a valid DHCPACK. False otherwise.
